description:
CORRECTNESS: Context encoding for MAC_2 and MAC_3 verification ignores CBOR encoding errors.

Locations in edhoc_initiator_process_msg2:
- Lines 601-606: context_2 encoding for MAC_2 - no error checks
- Lines 646-650: context_3 encoding for MAC_3 - no error checks

Code:
ZCBOR_STATE_E(zse_ctx2, 0, context_2, sizeof(context_2), 0);
zcbor_bstr_encode_ptr(zse_ctx2, ctx->c_r, ctx->c_r_len);
zcbor_bstr_encode_ptr(zse_ctx2, peer_pubkey, 32);
zcbor_bstr_encode_ptr(zse_ctx2, ctx->th_2, 32);
zcbor_bstr_encode_ptr(zse_ctx2, peer_pubkey, 32);
size_t context_2_len = zse_ctx2->payload - context_2;

If any zcbor call fails, context_2_len will be wrong, and MAC verification will fail mysteriously.

Same pattern in edhoc_responder_process_msg1 (lines 920-926) and edhoc_responder_process_msg3 (lines 1099-1103).

Fix: Check return values of all zcbor calls and return appropriate error.

File: lichen/subsys/lichen/edhoc/edhoc.c:601-606,646-650,920-926,1099-1103
